    The pros are they are actually wide enough to where they don't bother the sides of my feet or my toes. There's more wiggle room with the same side and wide width shoes compared to the other shoes of this brand. I've also noticed that the shoes are kind of water resistant. It takes a lot of water in order for them to get soaked. They seem to dry off quickly as well. I tend to get hospital grade cleaners on my shoes. I have used bleach wipes on the shoes and it doesn't seem to affect them as well. The shoes are definitely very durable. Compared to the other shoes these don't really get rocks stuck at the bottom of them when walking outside. The floors at work don't feel like they're grabbing me. Which is good.

    The cons compared to the cheaper shoes from this exact brand, they're not as comfortable. It would be nice to have more comfort for the bottom of my feet. Even though I have gotten used to their not being much support on the bottom of my feet, it would still be nice to have a little bit more. One of my worst cons is, trying to clean them. Once you get any sort of bad odor in them, good luck getting that out.
